references: Since the performance of an algorithm may fluctuate during training, we are interested in comparing the methods in the best performance they achieved during training. To do so, we save the model generated by each method at the iteration where the highest accuracy is achieved on the validation data. Then, we report the performance of the saved model’s by each method on the testing set in Table 1. Again, we show the results when p0subscript𝑝0p_{0} is the distribution of the majority and the minority groups separately. Our method outperforms the baselines in most of the cases.
